A motorist drove their car for two months after the airbags had deployed, police said.Officers pulled the driver over near South Mimms on the A1(M) in Hertfordshire on Saturday.They said the "driver admitted to have been driving with all airbags deployed and a huge cracked windscreen for over two months".The motorist was reported to court and told the car was unfit to be driven until it was fixed.
